## What this is

A self-contained `docker compose` stack with:

{% for c in stack.components -%}
- `{{ c }}`
{% endfor %}

Envoy sits at the front edge and rewrites Databricks-shaped URLs so the same
code paths work locally and on Databricks. For example:

```
http://localhost:${ENVOY_PORT}/api/2.0/mlflow/experiments/create
```

… is routed to MLflow's `/mlflow/api/2.0/mlflow/experiments/create` endpoint,
exactly as Databricks would route it to its managed MLflow.

## Quickstart

```bash
# 1. Copy the env file and edit as needed
cp .env.example .env.local

# 2. Bring up the stack
just up

# 3. Open the UIs
{% if 'local-stack-envoy' in stack.components -%}
just mlflow-ui      # http://localhost:${ENVOY_PORT}/mlflow
just uc-ui          # http://localhost:${ENVOY_PORT}/unity-catalog
just notebooks      # http://localhost:${ENVOY_PORT}/notebooks
{%- else -%}
docker compose ps
{%- endif %}
```

